info.name: RMS REST API
info.description:
# Introduction The RMS REST API acts as a gateway to the RMS database. It can be used to extract and update a broad subset of data for a range of uses. The information can be extracted periodically as an automated routine or on demand. This interface also allows for the updating and creation of new data as well as the posting of charges. The interface also allows for posting data back to RMS. This interface also allows for the updating and creation of new data as well as the posting of charges. This document describes the protocol for the exchange of information between the Property Management System (RMS) and third-Party Applications. For information about the costs involved, please [click here](https://www.rmscloud.com/technical-support/developers/) There are many uses for the REST API, please click on any any of the links below for more information on how to complete your integration: - E-marketing solutions - Loyalty systems - Data correlation for group wide reporting - Statistical reporting - Data Warehouse - [POS](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/images/websiteWorkflow.png) - KIOSK - [Website](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/images/websiteWorkflow.png) - [Postman](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/postman_collection.json) # Getting Access to the API 1. Register for a partner account. [Partner Portal](https://partnerportal.rmscloud.com/Login) 2. Contact RMS Sales (sales@rmscloud.com) and request the API Developers Kit ($550 excl. GST) 3. Once payment has been processed the API Support Team will contact you with login details so you may start developing. 4. Use the credentials provided along with the [POST authToken call](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/#section/connecting%20and%20authentication) to create a token. 5. Click `Authorize` in the documentation and enter your token to test the calls. 6. If you have any further questions that are not covered in the spec, please contact apisupport@rmscloud.com # Certification We do not require certification for your integration to go live as you are responsible for changing and maintaining your integration.

As an alternative solution, we suggest you coordinate with the mutual client to arrange a BETA Period.

Partners also have the option of working with a copy of clients Live data in an environment we call 'Training'. This will allow you to perform a certification with them, without impacting their Live data.

You can point your integration to a clients training environment by setting the parameter 'useTrainingDatabase' to 'true' when creating a token with Live agent credentials and the customer Client credentials. # Guidelines and Formatting 1. Any reference to number as 'no' in RMS will be referred to as 'id' in the API. 2. Any reference to the term 'Made' in RMS will be referred to as 'Created' in the API. 3. Default mandatory fields will be identified; however, clients may configure their own mandatory fields. 4. All examples will be shown in order of Basic, Full, Lite. The Basic object will be returned by default. 5. All code is written in lower camelCase. 6. Date format YEAR-MONTH-DAY HOUR-MINUTE-SECOND E.g. "2016-08-22 19:25:00". 7. When performing a PUT you first need to perform a GET on the Full Object, then alter the fields then perform the PUT with the whole object. If you pass back blank fields the original fields will be changed to 'Null'. 8. When using the POST function always pass 'id' as '0' to create the next available record. # Frequently Asked Questions **Q: Why can’t I see the name of an object in my call?** *A: We will only return the 'id' for most table references. To retrieve additional data you will need to pass that 'id' via the appropriate GET call.* **Q: How can I find the Room Number ?** *A: Any reference to Room No, Site No, Dock No will be referred to as Area.* **Q: How can I find the name of the room types?** *A: Any reference to Room Type, Site Type, Dock Type will be referred to as Category.* **Q: What time zone are the time stamps returned in?** *A: All references to Date/Time are returned in local property time.* **Q: Is there a limit to how many records are returned?** *A: All GET functions will return a default limit of 100 records ordered by the Id field. This limit can be increased and/or multiple calls can be performed using the offset parameter.* **Q: Why is my guest returned with an Account Id of '0'?** *A: If a guest has never charged back to their account id before, it will not exist in RMS. Use the call '/guests/createAccountId' to create an Account id for a guest.* **Q: Why are my online notifications not triggering?** *A: The REST API will not trigger Online notifications. If you require an internal or external email to be sent to guests, this will need to be setup as a triggered corrospondence. [Click here for more info](https://helpcentre.rmscloud.com/triggered-correspondence-setup/triggered-correspondence)* **Q: What do I do if am returned an ID with the value of '0' e.g. marketSegmentID: 0** *A: If a value of 0 is returned this is the equivalent of Null* # High Level RMS Relationship Schema ![Schema](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/images/rms-schema.png) # Status Error Responses: - 400: Bad Request - 401: Unauthorized - 403: Forbidden - 404: Not Found - 406: Not Acceptable # Alternate Format: - [Three column format](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/) - [Postman](https://restapidocs.rmscloud.com/postman_collection.json) # Rate Limiting: RMS enforces rate limiting as per the following rules: - rmscloud.com/authToken - 10 requests per 60 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/reservations* - 100 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/reservations/search - 60 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/reservations/id/dailyRevenue - 30 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/availabilityrategrid - 60 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/availableAreas - 40 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/guest/id - 30 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/reservations/id/regoaccess - 100 requests per 60 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/areas* - 30 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds - rmscloud.com/rates/rateQuote - 40 requests per 10 sec, block for 60 seconds Please note that our REST API uses JSON format

item.name: Retrieve a properties availability and rate information based on additionals to present in a grid

request.description:
The agent ID in the availabilityrategrid call refers to the ID of existing channels the property is connected too.

You will need to use the 'GET/onlineAgents' call to retrieve the list of connected channels at the property, confirm with the client which one they would like to use, then use the ID for that channel in the 'agentId' field of the availabilityrategrid call.

To determine the Rate ID to pass for the associated agent ID you must use the call 'GET/agents/{id}/rates'.

If you set the parameter 'includeEstimatedRates' to true this option will return an estimated rate value. This value may not reflect the same value as the final quote check. Estimated rates can be identified in the response by the value 'estimatedRate: True' (This value will only appear in the response body if this parameter is set to 'True')

item.name: This call allows you to make a RMSPay Payment against a guest.

request.description:
Processing an RMSPay payment has to be done in 3 steps:

1. Use this call to process a payment via the RMSPay Gateway.

2. You would then need to grab the redirect URL, to obtain the payment details (card details, merchant reference, token reference etc)

3. Then use these details on the POST/transactions/receipt call to pass this payment into RMS.

request.description:
The room type holds the room description, number of guests it can accommodate, price, etc. Your property may have multiple rooms (or units) that all are of the same room type. You can add and edit room types and units in Settings -> Accommodation. A room type named “Double room”.

Any reference to Room Type, Site Type, Dock Type will be referred to as Category. Categories are created by the property and all fields are not necessary configured with information. If a particular field is required for your integration and you receive a null value you will need to ask the property directly to populate this.

Max occupants’ can be set at a category level and at an Area Level. When calculating max occupants adults and children do count toward max occupants, but infants do not.

request.description:
This call allows you to retrieve up to 1 days availability per call, however you can pass multiple calls in parallel within the rate limit restrictions (see rate limiting section of documentation for more info on rate limits).

The agent ID in the availabilityrategrid call refers to the ID of existing channels the property is connected too.

You will need to use the 'GET/onlineAgents' call to retrieve the list of connected channels at the property, confirm with the client which one they would like to use, then use the ID for that channel in the 'agentId' field of the availabilityrategrid call.

request.description:
This call allows you to retrieve up to 14 days availability per call, however you can pass multiple calls in parallel within the rate limit restrictions (see rate limiting section of documentation for more info on rate limits).

The agent ID in the availabilityrategrid call refers to the ID of existing channels the property is connected too.

You will need to use the 'GET/onlineAgents' call to retrieve the list of connected channels at the property, confirm with the client which one they would like to use, then use the ID for that channel in the 'agentId' field of the availabilityrategrid call.

To determine the Rate ID to pass for the associated agent ID you must use the call 'GET/agents/{id}/rates'.

If you set the parameter 'includeEstimatedRates' to true this option will return an estimated rate value. This value may not reflect the same value as the final quote check. Estimated rates can be identified in the response by the value 'estimatedRate: True' (This value will only appear in the response body if this parameter is set to 'True')

item.name: Allow RMS to provide you with Live availability, rates and inventory. - This is not a working API call and is for documentational purposes only

request.description:
This call is for documentational purposes only - please read the information below for more detials.

If your integration requires you to disply more than 14 days availability to customers than RMS suggest that we list you as a channel so that we may provide you with Live ARI (Availabilty, rates and invientory). This solution will require you to build a local cache so you are able to host the data we provide you.
To complete this process please follow the steps below:

1. Please raise a Service Request via the partner portal to have this setup.
2.The team will respond with questions and once the relevant information is provided, this will take roughly 2 - 3 weeks to be implemented.

request.description:
For testing purposes please use the test credentials in the example and change the ‘Module type’ to the one you have been advised with your Live credentials. Live agent credentials will not work with the test database ‘11281’.

e.g.
{
'agentId': 15,
'agentPassword': '1h&29$vk449f8',
'clientId': 11281,
'clientPassword': '6k!Dp$N4',
'useTrainingDatabase': false,
'moduleType': ['Your module type/s goes here']
}

Tokens have an expiry of 12 hours, tokens expiry times are displayed in UTC.

The credentials provided in the example of this call are test credentials and can be used to create your integration prior to obtaining Live credentials

Live Agent credentials (Agent id, Agent Password & Module type are provided upon purchase of the developer’s kit. Live Client credentials (Client id and Client Password are provided by the mutual client after they purchase the appropriate module from RMS.
